High-quality data refers to data with a data quality score above 80; 
Validated data points are those with a validation status of 'validated'; 
Abundant data refers to dates with more than 10 validated data points.

; Wholesale electricity price (WEP) refers to the price at which electricity is sold from a wholesale market to a retail market.; 
; Quality checks are evaluations to ensure the data's accuracy and reliability.; 
; Access patterns refer to the logs of who accessed the data and when.; 
; Cumulative price here means the running total of wholesale electricity prices over time within each period.; 
; Ranking is based on the wholesale electricity price in descending order, showing the highest price first within each period.
